This map was made similar to my origonal shootsalot maps. Although this one is much smaller, doesn't have a bomb site or hostages, and has much better lighting and overall looks better. Just like the origonal, I put a building in and made it possible to go under the building and also on top to the roof. 

The much smaller size of this map, as opposed to the origonals, makes it better for use in games such as gungame. The origonals were far too big for this sort of gameplay and would be much more suited as a deathmatch map.

I also included rain in this map to give it a bit more of a realistic effect. 

I also included a .nav file to have fun with bots with. Although using this map with bots was a mistake for me. I tried it and really got beaten really badly with the bots set on easy. Bots seem to be really good on this map.

Well, I hope you like it. Try it out and assess it.

I've wanted to make a map based off of a boat or a ship for quite some time. I had a dream a few days ago that really just pushed me to make the map. The story of how the dream went is written below to give you an idea of why I set it up the way I did.

The dream started out with a small group of navy seals (CTs) search for a boat that may be smuggling stolen goods from the US to somewhere around the italy area to be sold for other things. The CTs searched all night for the terrorists who were stealing the goods, the sun started to rise and the strong haze of the fog surrounded them. Momentarily, they lost their sense of direction but soon they got a radio call saying that an air search unit spotted an unfamiliar ship holding up in a small cove where the fog was the thickest. By the time the CTs arrived to the cove the terrorists realized that they have been found and scramble from their bunks onto the ship's deck. The ct's had pulled their boats close up to the ship and realized there were ropes hanging down from the side of the ship, they all climbed up the boat and infiltrated the terrorists. The CTs killed all of the terrorists in the boat and took over the ship. and that's the end of it.

MISSION:

Terrorists:
You hear the CTs comming abord the ship and you must scramble to the deck, or find a place to hide inside the ship. Eliminate all of the Counter Terrorists before they take the cargo you are stealing.

Counter Terrorists:
Jump off your boat and climb up the ropes on the side of the ship and infiltrate the terrorists before they find out you're there. Eliminate any and all threats you find on the boat and take the stolen cargo back to where it belongs.

fy_senso is exactly like fy_iceworld, except it is indoors in a school like eviroment.  

Up to 24 players can play at once but is better for 16 players (8v8)

of sorts.  

You can climb on top of the classrooms anywhere you see a vent. Be aware that the main ceiling
is to low to jump from ceiling to ceiling.  This is no mistake but done in an effort to shorten
round times be avoiding a standoff where players can't find each other.

A small, fast paced map set in an urban setting. Takes place in a self-storage facility, where terrorists were discovered to have been using to store up weapons and ammunition. Counter-terrorists respond to the threat.


 The map features a .nav file for play with bots, as well as a 3D Skybox and color correction.


 Please let me know of any issues, whether aesthetic or gameplay related.

This is my 4th released map.

It takes place in one of those self-storage compounds. (In this case a high security one because for 46 lockers there are 2 offices and 2 guard stations)

The entire map is as mirrored as I could make it but it's off by a few small, unimportant inches. Of the 46 lockers the players can get into 6 of the 8 open ones. There is access to the rooftops but there is little cover there. In addition there are a few vehicles.

STORY:
I guess you can't have much of a story when it comes to FY_ maps but I can imagine that the Ts have broken into the compound in an attempt to steal something.
Dunno ;] Just have fun :9 and please comment!

I'm finally mapping for Source again! This is probably my first source map in like, 2 years. It's a simple, COD4 inspired map I made to just fool around in, nothing to extravagant. I had to do a lot of re-compiling before this release. Also, I would have put HDR in, but every time I tried, the map would look terrible (Yes, I built my cubemaps. Once with HR on, and once with HDR off). So, I guess I'll just have to put HDR in my next releases. .nav, .bsp and .txt are packaged in the rar file. Also, cubemaps are built. Any issues, please tell me about. These can range from visual blemishes, to gameplay issues. Have fun.
